&lt;p>In this case you can see that &lt;code>data_len&lt;/code> is 0.
This is because our payload is very small.
So it doesn&amp;rsquo;t require the kernel to allocate pages to accomodate the data.
Instead if we look at &lt;code>len&lt;/code> we will see that the data is of length &lt;code>156&lt;/code>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>I do not know how all the 28 header bytes here are formatted, but if I figure it out, I will come back and update this section.&lt;/p>
