loading="lazy"
alt="High level overview"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Just creating a massive packet isn&amp;rsquo;t enough to trigger the vulnerability, at least not in my testing.
There are a few checks that must be passed.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>A page is &lt;code>0x1000&lt;/code> bytes, or &lt;code>4096&lt;/code> in decimal.
Another thing to keep in mind, the patch defines the max size as &lt;code>(PAGE_SIZE &amp;lt;&amp;lt; SKB_FRAG_PAGE_ORDER)&lt;/code>, and from the source code we can figure out that &lt;code>SKB_FRAG_PAGE_ORDER&lt;/code> is &lt;code>15&lt;/code>.
So the max size here is:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
