&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">(4096 &amp;lt;&amp;lt; 15) = 0x8000000 bytes
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>We also have to account for the &lt;code>28&lt;/code> bytes of header probably.
Anyways, tracking the &lt;code>allocsize&lt;/code> variable in &lt;code>esp_output_head&lt;/code>, we see that it gets used in &lt;code>skb_page_frag_refill&lt;/code>.
We can ignore the &lt;code>unlikely()&lt;/code> that wraps it, this is just an optimization.&lt;/p>
