&lt;p>The buffer cannot be generated with &lt;code>skb_cloned()&lt;/code> and is not one of multiple shared copies of the buffer.
Cloned buffers are shared data so must not be written to under normal circumstances.
There are a lot of situations in which an &lt;code>skb&lt;/code> might get cloned, and during testing, I was able to get past this check fairly often, so I didn&amp;rsquo;t come up with a specific strategy hear other than run and pray.&lt;/p>
