&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> &lt;span class="p">...&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>&lt;code>skb_tailroom&lt;/code> will return 0 if the data of &lt;code>skb&lt;/code> paginated, when happens for big payloads.
Since we need our payload to be big and paginated, then we must ensure that &lt;code>esp-&amp;gt;tailen&lt;/code> is GREATER 0, otherwise entering this branch will not allocate the buffer we need.
The &lt;code>tailen&lt;/code> value represents the length of the &lt;code>ESP&lt;/code> trailer in an &lt;code>ESP&lt;/code> packet.
This means that this check should often be easy to pass, as there should always be info attached to an &lt;code>ESP&lt;/code> packet.
